{"title_page": "Portugal national under-19 basketball team", "text_new": "{{Infobox national basketball team\n| country            = Portugal \n| logo               = Flag of Portugal.svg\n| logo_width         = 130px \n| nickname           = \n| fiba_zone          = FIBA Europe\n| national_fed       = [[Portuguese Basketball Federation|Federa\u00e7\u00e3o Portuguesa de Basquetebol]]\n| coach              = \n| wc_championship    = [[FIBA Under-19 Basketball World Cup|Under-19 World Cup]]\n| wc_appearances     = 1 (1999) \n| wc_medals          = None\n| zone_championship  = [[FIBA U18 European Championship|U18 European Championship]]\n| zone_appearances   = None\n| zone_medals        = \n| zone_championship2 = [[FIBA U18 European Championship#Division B|U18 European Championship Division B]]\n| zone_appearances2  = 15\n| zone_medals2       = {{Eur3}} ''Bronze:'' ([[2006 FIBA Europe Under-18 Championship Division B|2006]])\n| h_body             = ffffff \n| h_shorts           = ffffff \n| h_pattern_b        = _greensides \n| h_pattern_s        = _greensides \n| a_body             = 990000 \n| a_shorts           = 990000\n| a_pattern_b        = _greensides \n| a_pattern_s        = _greensides \n}}\n\nThe '''Portugal national under-18 and under-19 basketball team''' is the national representative for [[Portugal]] in international under-18 and under-19 [[basketball]] competitions. They are controlled by the [[Portuguese Basketball Federation|Federa\u00e7\u00e3o Portuguesa de Basquetebol]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Portugal (U18-U19)|url=https://www.eurobasket.com/Portugal/basketball-National-Team.asp?Age=18|accessdate=15 October 2019}}</ref> \n\nThe team competes at the [[FIBA U18 European Championship]], with an chance to qualify for the [[FIBA Under-19 Basketball World Cup|FIBA Under-19 World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Portugal at the 2016 FIBA U18 European Championship Division B|url=https://www.fiba.basketball/europe/u18b/2016/Portugal|accessdate=7 August 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Portugal at the 2017 FIBA U18 European Championship Division B|url=https://www.fiba.basketball/europe/u18b/2017/Portugal|accessdate=19 August 2017}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*[[Portugal national basketball team]]\n*[[Portugal national under-17 basketball team]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.fpb.pt/ Official website] {{in lang|pt}}\n*[http://www.fiba.basketball/federation/Portugal FIBA profile]\n\n{{International youth basketball}}\n{{National sports teams of Portugal}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Portugal national basketball team}}\n[[Category:Basketball in Portugal]]\n[[Category:National under-18 basketball teams]]\n[[Category:National under-19 basketball teams]]\n[[Category:National sports teams of Portugal|Basketball]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox national basketball team\n| country            = Portugal \n| logo               = Flag of Portugal.svg\n| logo_width         = 130px \n| nickname           = \n| fiba_zone          = FIBA Europe\n| national_fed       = [[Portuguese Basketball Federation|Federa\u00e7\u00e3o Portuguesa de Basquetebol]]\n| coach              = \n| wc_championship    = [[FIBA Under-19 Basketball World Cup|Under-19 World Cup]]\n| wc_appearances     = 1 (1999) \n| wc_medals          = None\n| zone_championship  = [[FIBA U18 European Championship|U18 European Championship]]\n| zone_appearances   = None\n| zone_medals        = \n| zone_championship2 = [[FIBA U18 European Championship#Division B|U18 European Championship Division B]]\n| zone_appearances2  = 15\n| zone_medals2       = {{Eur3}} ''Bronze:'' ([[2006 FIBA Europe Under-18 Championship Division B|2006]])\n| h_body             = ffffff \n| h_shorts           = ffffff \n| h_pattern_b        = _greensides \n| h_pattern_s        = _greensides \n| a_body             = 990000 \n| a_shorts           = 990000\n| a_pattern_b        = _greensides \n| a_pattern_s        = _greensides \n}}\n\nThe '''Portugal national under-18 and under-19 basketball team