eline |title=Bohol exec wants isolation area in every barangay |url=https://www.pna.gov.ph/articles/1098307 |accessdate=April 1, 2020 |work=Philippine News Agency |date=March 31, 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n**[[Cebu]]<ref name=\"ABSCBN-CovidCebu\">{{cite news |title=Cebu records 1st case of COVID-19 |url=https://news.abs-cbn.com/news/03/18/20/cebu-records-1st-case-of-covid-19 |accessdate=March 31, 2020 |work=ABS-CBN News |date=March 18, 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n**''[[Cebu City]]''<ref name=\"YahooPHNews-CovidCebuCity\">{{cite news |title=Cebu City \u2018now has 19 Covid cases\u2019 |url=https://ph.news.yahoo.com/cebu-city-now-19-covid-160400370.html |accessdate=March 31, 2020 |work=Yahoo! News Philippines |publisher=SunStar |date=March 29, 2020 |language=en-PH}}</ref>\n**''[[Lapu-Lapu, Cebu|Lapu-Lapu]]''<ref name=\"YahooPHNews-CovidCebuCity\" />\n**''[[Mandaue]]''<ref name=\"CNNPH-CovidMandaue\">{{cite news |title=COVID-19 reaches Cebu as Mandaue City confirms first case |url=http://www.cnnphilippines.com/regional/2020/3/18/Cebu-Mandaue-City-COVID-19-coronavirus.html |accessdate=March 31, 2020 |work=CNN Philippines |date=March 18, 2020 |language=en}}</ref><ref name=\"YahooPHNews-CovidCebuCity\" />\n**[[Negros Oriental]]<ref name=\"MB-CovidNegrosOr\">{{cite news |last1=Masculino |first1=Glazyl |title=1 positive case of COVID-19 reported in Negros Oriental |url=https://news.mb.com.ph/2020/03/12/1-positive-case-of-covid-19-reported-in-negros-oriental/ |accessdate=March 31, 2020 |work=Manila Bulletin |date=March 12, 2020}}</ref>\n*[[Eastern Visayas]] (Region VIII)\n**[[Northern Samar]]{{refn|group=note|name=Northern Samar case|Only case admitted in Tacloban.<ref name=\"PNAGovPH-CovidLeyte\">{{cite news |last1=Meniano |first1=Sarwell |title=DOH confirms first Covid-19 case in Eastern Visayas |url=https://www.pna.gov.ph/articles/1097553 |accessdate=March 31, 2020 |work=Philippine News Agency |date=March 23, 2020 |language=en}}</ref>}}\n**[[Samar]]{{refn|group=note|name=Samar case|Only case admitted in Tacloban.<ref name=secondcaseWV/>}}\n**''[[Tacloban]]''{{refn|group=note|name=Tacloban cases|All two cases imported from another locality; Northern Samar<ref name=\"PNAGovPH-CovidLeyte\"/> and Samar<ref name=secondcaseWV/>}}\n*[[Zamboanga Peninsula]] (Region IX)\n**''[[Zamboanga City]]''<ref name=\"MB-CovidZamboangaCity\">{{cite news |last1=Lacson |first1=Nonoy |title=First COVID-19 patient confirmed in Zamboanga City |url=https://news.mb.com.ph/2020/03/25/first-covid-19-patient-confirmed-in-zamboanga-city/ |accessdate=March 31, 2020 |work=Manila Bulletin |date=March 25, 2020}}</ref>\n**[[Zamboanga del Sur]]<ref>{{cite news |title=Zamboanga del Sur reports first two COVID-19 cases |url=https://www.cnnphilippines.com/regional/2020/3/30/Zamboanga-del-Sur-first-coronavirus-cases.html |accessdate=March 30, 2020 |work=CNN Philippine |date=March 30, 2020}}</ref>\n*[[Northern Mindanao]] (Region X)\n**[[Camiguin]]<ref>{{cite news |title=Camiguin logs first COVID-19 case |url=https://cnnphilippines.com/regional/2020/4/5/covid-19-camiguin-jj-romualdo.html |accessdate=April 5, 2020 |work=CNN Philippines |date=April 5, 2020}}</ref>\n**''[[Cagayan de Oro]]''<ref>{{cite news |title=Calamba, Cagayan de Oro report first cases of COVID-19 |url=https://cnnphilippines.com/news/2020/3/25/Philippines-cities-provinces-first-cases-COVID-19.html?fbclid=IwAR2sGxWcoZqVAzYGxaAjFYQl51801JWiKdTkNPwFezr4oVuexiqQ2yNin1k |accessdate=April 1, 2020 |work=CNN Philippines |date=March 25, 2020}}</ref>\n**''[[Iligan]]''<ref>{{cite news |title=Iligan City records 1st COVID-19 case |url=https://news.mb.com.ph/2020/03/25/iligan-city-records-1st-covid-19-case/ |accessdate=April 3, 2020 |work=Manila Bulletin |date=March 25, 2020}}</ref>\n**[[Lanao del Norte]]<ref name=\"Inquirer-CovidLanaoDelNorte\">{{cite news |last1=Umel |first1=Richel |title=Entire village in Lanao Norte on lockdown after resident tests positive for COVID-19 |url=https://newsinfo.inquirer.net/1251150/entire-village-in-lanao-norte-on-lockdown-after-resident-tests-positive-for-covid-19 |accessdate=March 31, 2020 |work=Philippine Daily Inquirer |date=March 30, 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n**[[Misamis Occidental]]<ref>{{cite news |title=Mayor confirms first COVID-19 case in Ozamiz City |url=https://newsinfo.inquirer.net/1250574/mayor-confirms-first-covid-19-case-in-ozamiz-city |accessdate=April 3, 2020 |work=Philippine Daily Inquirer |date=March 29, 2020}}</ref>\n*[[Davao Region]] (Region XI)\n**''[[Davao City]]''<ref name=\"MB-CovidDavaoCity\">{{cite news |title=2 COVID-19 cases confirmed in Davao City |url=https://news.mb.com.ph/2020/03/22/2-covid-19-cases-confirmed-in-davao-city/ |accessdate=March 31, 2020 |work=Manila Bulletin |date=March 22, 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"MB-CovidDavaoRegion\" />\n**[[Davao de Oro]]<ref name=\"MB-CovidDavaoRegion\">{{cite news |last1=Valdez |first1=Warren |title=Davao Region COVID-19 Update: 50 positive cases; six fatalities |url=https://news.mb.com.ph/2020/03/31/davao-region-covid-19-update-50-positive-cases-six-fatalities/ |accessdate=March 31, 2020 |work=Manila Bulletin |date=March 31, 2020}}</ref>\n**[[Davao del Norte]]<ref name=\"MB-CovidDavaoRegion\" />\n**[[Davao del Sur]]<ref name=\"MB-CovidDavaoRegion\" />\n**[[Davao Oriental]]<ref name=\"MB-CovidDavaoRegion\" />\n*[[Soccsksargen]] (Region XII)\n**[[South Cotabato]]<ref name=\"PNAGovPH-CovidSouthCotabato\">{{cite news |last1=Osano |first1=Roel |title=South Cotabato confirms 1st positive Covid-19 case |url=https://www.pna.gov.ph/articles/1098326 |accessdate=March 31, 2020 |work=Philippine News Agency |date=March 31, 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n**[[Sultan Kudarat]]<ref>{{cite news |title=With confirmed COVID-19 case, Sultan Kudarat to impose lockdown, curfew |url=https://www.mindanews.com/top-stories/2020/03/with-confirmed-covid-19-case-sultan-kudarat-to-impose-lockdown-curfew/ |accessdate=March 30, 2020 |work=MindaNews |date=March 27, 2020}}</ref>\n*[[Caraga]] (Region XIII)\n**''[[Butuan]]''<ref>{{cite news|url=https://cnnphilippines.com/regional/2020/4/6/caraga-all-regions-covid-19-cases.html|title=Caraga reports first COVID-19 case|work=CNN Philippines|date=April 6, 2020|accessdate=April 6, 2020}}</ref>\n*[[Bangsamoro]] (BARMM)\n**''[[Cotabato City]]''<ref name=\"PIAGovPH-CovidCotabatoCity\">{{cite news |title=Cotabato City records first COVID 19 case in R12 |url=https://pia.gov.ph/news/articles/1036522 |accessdate=March 31, 2020 |work=Philippine Information Agency |agency=PIA Cotabato City |date=March 18, 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n**[[Lanao del Sur]]<ref name=\"ABS-CBN-CovidLanaoDelSur\">{{cite news |last1=Butardo |first1=Maria Cecilia |title=COVID-19 positive patient dies in Lanao del Sur |url=https://news.abs-cbn.com/news/03/17/20/covid-19-positive-patient-dies-in-lanao-del-sur |accessdate=March 31, 2020 |work=ABS-CBN News |date=March 17, 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n{{div col end}}\n\n== Notes ==\n{{reflist|group=note}}\n\n== See also ==\n* [[2009 flu pandemic in the Philippines]]\n\n{{Portal bar|COVID-19|Philippines|Medicine|Viruses}}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|colwidth=30em}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{commons category}}\n* [http://www.covid19.gov.ph/ Philippine Government's Online Portal for the COVID-19 pandemic].\n* [https://ncovtracker.doh.gov.ph/ COVID-19 case and situation tracker] by the [[Department of Health (Philippines)|Department of Health]]\n* [https://corona.arrangy.com Worldwide Coronavirus Map, confirmed Cases] \u2013 Map the route paths of coronavirus confirmed cases.\n* [https://endcov.ph/dashboard/ University of the Philippines COVID-19 case tracker]\n* [https://covid19ph.com/ Unofficial COVID-19 Philippines data and case tracker]\n\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic}}\n{{2020 coronavirus pandemic in the Philippines}}\n{{Rodrigo Duterte}}\n\n[[Category:2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic by country and territory|Philippines]]\n[[Category:2020 disasters in the Philippines|coronavirus pandemic]]\n[[Category:Medical outbreaks in the Philippines]]\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in Asia|Philippines]]\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in the Philippines| ]]\n", "name_user": "Otis20x", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eLockdowns", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_coronavirus_pandemic_in_the_Philippines"}
{"title_page": "Andr\u00e9 Schiffrin", "text_new": "{{Use mdy dates|date=December 2013}}\n{{Infobox writer <!-- For more information see [[:Template:Infobox Writer/doc]]. --> \n| name          = Andr\u00e9 Schiffrin\n| image         = \n| image_size    = \n| alt           = \n| caption       = \n| pseudonym     = \n| birth_name    = \n| birth_date    = {{Birth date|1935|6|14|mf=y}}\n| birth_place   = [[Paris]], France\n| death_date    = {{Death date and age|2013|12|1|1935|6|14|mf=y}}\n| death_place   = [[Paris]], France\n| resting_place = \n| occupation    = Writer and editor\n| language      = \n| nationality   = French\n| citizenship   = American\n| education     = \n| alma_mater    = [[Yale University]]<br />[[University of Cambridge]]\n| period        = \n| genre         = \n| subject       = \n| movement      = \n| notableworks  = \n| spouse        = {{marriage|Maria Elena de la Iglesia|1961|2013}}\n| partner       = \n| children      = [[Anya Schiffrin]], Natalia Schiffrin\n| relatives     = \n| awards        = \n| signature     = \n| signature_alt = \n| module        =\n| website       = <!-- www.example.com -->\n| portaldisp    = \n}}\n'''Andr\u00e9 Schiffrin''' (June 14, 1935 \u2013 December 1, 2013)<!-- See note at the foot of the following source for the correction. --><ref name=\"McFadden\">Robert D. McFadden [https://www.nytimes.com/2013/12/02/books/andre-schiffrin-publishing-force-and-a-founder-of-new-press-is-dead-at-78.html \"Andr\u00e9 Schiffrin, Publishing Force and a Founder of New Press, Is Dead at 78\"], ''New York Times'', December 1, 2013</ref>  was a French-born American author, publisher and socialist.\n\n== Life ==\nSchiffrin was born in Paris, the son of Jacques Schiffrin, a Russian [[Jew]] who emigrated to France and briefly enjoyed success there as publisher of the ''[[Biblioth\u00e8que de la Pl\u00e9iade]]'', which he founded, and which was bought by [[Gallimard]], until he was dismissed because of the [[anti-Jewish]] laws enforced by the [[Vichy regime]]. Jacques Schiffrin and his family had to flee and eventually found refuge in the United States. As the younger Schiffrin recalls in his autobiography, ''A Political Education: Coming of Age in Paris and New York'' (2007), he thus experienced life in two countries as a child of a European Jewish intellectual family.\n\nAs an anti-Communist socialist, Schiffrin opposed both the Soviet invasion of Czechoslovakia and the U.S. war in Vietnam. He was one of the founders of the organization that became [[Students for a Democratic Society (1960 organization)|Students for a Democratic Society]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.newyorker.com/magazine/2009/04/13/the-bush-six|title=The Bush Six|first=Jane|last=Mayer|website=The New Yorker}}</ref> In 1968, he signed the \"[[Writers and Editors War Tax Protest]]\" pledge, vowing to refuse tax payments in protest against the Vietnam War.<ref>\"Writers and Editors War Tax Protest\" January 30, 1968 ''New York Post''</ref>\n\nSchiffrin was the managing director of publishing at [[Pantheon Books]], where he was partially responsible for introducing the works of [[Boris Pasternak|Pasternak]], [[Michel Foucault|Foucault]] and others to [[United States|American]] readers. Schiffrin's 28-year period at Pantheon, a division of Random House, came to an end in 1990 when CEO Alberto Vitale sacked him because of a conflict over the division's losses and the downsizing which Vitale wished to make.<ref name=\"McFadden\"/>\n\nIn 1992 Schiffrin, with former Pantheon colleague Diane Wachtell, established the non-profit [[The New Press]],<ref name=\"McFadden\"/> explaining that he did so because of economic trends that prevented him from publishing the serious books he thought should be made available. Schiffrin discussed what he regards as the crisis in western publishing in his book ''The Business of Books: How the International Conglomerates Took Over Publishing and Changed the Way We Read'' (2000).\n\nIn 2011, Schiffrin was made a [[Legion of Honour|Chevalier of the L\u00e9gion d'honneur]] by the French government.<ref name=clh>{{cite web|last=Delattre|first=Fran\u00e7ois|title=Andr\u00e9 SCHIFFRIN Awarded Chevalier in the Order of the Legion of Honor|url=http://www.ambafrance-us.org/spip.php?article2914|publisher=French Embassy in the United States|accessdate=12 December 2013}}</ref>\n\nSchiffrin's daughter, journalist [[Anya Schiffrin]], is married to the economist and Nobel Prize winner [[Joseph Stiglitz]]. His daughter Natalia is married to international lawyer [[Philippe Sands]].\n\nSchiffrin died on December 1, 2013 in Paris from [[pancreatic cancer]].<ref name=\"McFadden\"/>\n\n== Works ==\n* ''L'\u00e9dition sans \u00e9diteurs'' (1999) {{ISBN|2-913372-02-3}}\n* ''The Business of Books: How the International Conglomerates Took Over Publishing and Changed the Way We Read'' (2000) {{ISBN|1-85984-362-X}} (Hardback {{ISBN|1-85984-763-3}})\n* ''Le contr\u00f4le de la parole'' (2005) {{ISBN|2-913372-35-X}}\n* ''A Political Education: Coming of Age in Paris and New York'' ([[Melville House Publishing]], 2007) {{ISBN|1-933633-15-8}}\n**Published in French as ''Allers-retours : Paris-New York, un itin\u00e9raire politique'' (2007) {{ISBN|2-86746-447-1}}\n**Published in German  ''Paris, New York und zur\u00fcck. Politische Lehrjahre eines Verlegers'', translated by Andrea Marenzeller; Matthes & Seitz, Berlin 2010 {{ISBN|978-3-88221-685-1}}\n* ''L'argent et les mots'' (2010) {{ISBN|978-2-35872-006-9}}\n* ''Words and Money'' ([[Verso Books]], 2010) {{ISBN|978-1-84467-680-4}}\n\nAlthough there exist no English versions of ''L'\u00e9dition sans \u00e9diteurs'' or ''Le contr\u00f4le de la parole'', there is some overlap of content between ''The Business of Books'' and the former.\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of English-language book publishing companies]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.thenewpress.com The New Press]\n* [http://www.mhpbooks.com Melville House]\n*